news.subject: 'Fast Forward': After Brief Halt of 2.5 Months, 9 New Vande Bharat Trains to Hit The Tracks on Sunday
news.newsDescription: After no new trains for at least two and a half months, the Indian Railways is all set to inaugurate nine Vande Bharats on Sunday in one go, including one for poll-bound Rajasthan, ministry officials told News18. The list of the trains that will be inaugurated also includes two each for West Bengals Howrah and Tamil Nadus Chennai. Kerala and Odisha will also each get a second train.
